1hit.content: The satellite will break if it gets hit one more time.

2hit.content: The satellite will break if it gets hit two more times.
Use your vortex control to set traps for the asteroids.

allBadges.content: Wow!  You collected all the badges.

badPhoto.content: but it didn't turn out very well.  Try again!

beginLevel1.content: We need to get Jet 2 to the park, so we can help clean it up.
First, we'll learn how to control him, so we can get him across this field.

beginLevel10.content: The things you need to take pictures of are shown with this symbol.
Aim your camera directly at them with your arm, and take the best photo you can,
so we an be studied later.

beginLevel11.content: Oh no!  Looks like another satellite is losing it's parts over Mars.
Pick them all up with your magnet, and take them to the bin.

beginLevel12.content: Oh wow!  More satellite pieces are falling.
Collect them with your magnet, and get them into the bin.
You'll get a special badge if you can keep most of them from hitting the ground.

beginLevel13.content: but there are some huge canyons in our way.
We have swapped out Boop's wheels with super wheels.
These new wheels will get Boop enough speed so she can jump over the canyons.

beginLevel14.content: There's a lot to do here:
Take photos, collect soil samples, and get
the last of the satellite parts into the bin.
You'll still need your super wheels as well.

beginLevel15.content: In order to fix the satellite, we need to bring back
all the parts that were lost from it.
Control the ship, and use the new tractor beam
to lift a bin off the ground and up toward space.

beginLevel16.content: Now we need to get to Mars.
There's a lot of space junk in our way though.
Carefully fly through it, and try not to bump into anything.
You'll get a special badge if you make it
to Mars without hitting a single obstacle.

beginLevel17.content: First, we need to get Boop to the other side of the tall rock formation,
so she can take her final soil sample.

beginLevel18.content: Now let's get all the parts of the satellite, so we can fix it.
There is a dense asteroid belt in our way though.
Use your robotic arm to push things out of your way,
so you can clear a path.

beginLevel19.content: Looks like there are five parts left that we still need.
Use your robotic arm and grab the parts and bring them back to the satellite.

beginLevel2.content: We're getting close to the park,
but there are some rocks in our way.

beginLevel20.content: but there's an asteroid storm approaching.
If 3 asteroids hit the satellite, it will break again!
Use the new vortex control to create traps for the asteroids
If an ateroid hits the trap, it will disappear.

beginLevel3.content: but it looks like there's some construction in our way.
Use your jump control at the very edge of the hole to get over it.

beginLevel4.content: We made it to the park.  Now let's help Jet 2 clean it up.
You'll have to use your vacuum to suck up the trash,
and then the ejector to throw it into the bin.

beginLevel5.content: Get the trash to the recycling bin.
Some of the trash is stuck in a tree!
You'll have to figure out how to get it down.

beginLevel6.content: I just got a message that there's a mysterious item stuck in a tree around here.
Let's try to get it out and see what it is.

beginLevel7.content: Looks like there's more than one satellite part around here.
Get them into the proper bin, but also make sure trash gets put away properly too.

binBeam.content: Great!  Now let's keep flying up and take the bin into space.

beginLevel9.content: Help Boop collect all the soil samples in this area.
There's also a new control available that will collect whatever is under her.

beginLevel8.content: We need to get Boop to certain places on Mars
to collect soil samples and take photos of interesting rock formations.
Use the new controls to help her get across these hills.

boopWrong.content: You need to pick her back up with your tractor beam
and set her down on the ground the right way.

break.content: Oh no!  The satellite is broken.

cantLeave.content: We still need to complete all of our missions.
Get Boop to the other side of the rock formation, get all the parts into the bin,
and then lift the bin into space.

canyon.content: You got stuck in the canyon.
Press the restart button to try this level again.

controlArmRotateCCW.content: This control makes Boop's arm rotate to the left.

controlArmRotateCW.content: This control makes Boop's arm rotate to the right.

controlCamera.content: This control equips a camera to Boop's arm.
Aim the camera and press the button again to take a photo.

controlCollectSoil.content: This control makes Boop collect soil when it's below her.

controlEject.content: This control makes Jet 2 throw whatever he has sucked up with his vacuum.

controlFlyDown.content: This control makes the ship fly down.

controlFlyLeft.content: This control makes the ship fly left.

controlFlyRight.content: This control makes the ship fly right.

controlFlyUp.content: This control makes the ship fly up.

controlJump.content: This control makes Jet 2 jump in the direction he's facing.

controlLeft.content: This control moves Jet 2 to the left.

controlMagnet.content: This control equips a magnet on Boop's arm
that tracks many things made out of metal.
Tapping it again will turn off the magnet.

controlRescue.content: This control rescues Boop if she flips over.

controlRight.content: This control moves Jet 2 to the right.

controlRoboticArm.content: This control makes the robotic arm appear.
It will grab whatever it touches, but will go back
into the ship if it can't find anything to grab.
Once it grabs something, press the control again to let go of it.
Press the control again to let go of it.

controlRotateCCW.content: This control makes Boop move to the left.

controlRotateCW.content: This control makes Boop move to the right.

controlSuperJump.content: This control makes Jet 2 super jump in the direction he's facing.

controlSuperWheels.content: This control activates Boop's super wheels.
With these wheels, you can go much faster than normal, and even take jumps!

controlThrottle.content: Press it once to shift into medium speed,
then press it again for high.
Press it a third time to switch back to low speed.

controlTractorBeam.content: This control activates the ship's Tractor Beam.
Position the ship above your target, and press the control to pick it up.
Then press the control again to drop it.

controlVacuum.content: This control makes Jet 2 suck up things around him.
Use the throw control to toss him back out.

descApple.content: An apple!  You can throw it to get things out of trees.

descAsteroid.content: An asteroid!  These are space rocks that come in all shapes and sizes.

descBird.content: A bird!  Sometimes these birds can carry things that we need for our missions.

descBoop.content: This is Boop. She's a rover that we'll control to complete all of the Mars missions.

descCompost.content: A compost bin.  You can throw rotten apples here.

descJet2.content: This is Jet 2.  He's on a mission to clean up the park.

descMars.content: This is Mars, the fourth planet from the Sun.

descPartBin.content: a bin!  Put satellite parts in this one.

descRecycleBin.content: a bin for trash and recycling.

descSatPart.content: a broken satellite part.  We need to find all of these so we can fix the satellite.

descSatellite.content: A satellite, this helps us quickly send information to and from Mars.

descSoil.content: A soil sample.  We study these to learn what Mars is made of.

descSpaceJunk.content: Space junk!  Avoid this if you can!

descStar.content: A star!  Try to find them hidden on every level.

descTrash.content: trash.  We need to help Jet 2 get these into the proper containers.

descVortex.content: an asteroid trap.  We use these to protect the satellite.

desctarget.content: something interesting to take a photo of.

doesntFit.content: You might have to rearrange the controls in the panel to make everything fit.

dontLeave.content: Don't leave Earth without the satellite part bin!

endSection1.content: You completed all the mission on Earth!
Now let's try some of the Mars levels and help Boop complete her missions also.

endSection2.content: Nice job!  You completed all of the Boop missions.
Now let's control the spaceship for the final set
of levels and fix the satellite near Mars.

endSection3.content: You did it!  You saved the satellite and completed all the missions for Jet 2,
Have you collected all the stars and badges yet?

hint1.content: If you're having trouble getting the trash down from the tree,
maybe try throwing something to knock it down.

hint2.content: Hmm.... Looks like that bird has what we need.
Maybe you could try to communicate with him somehow?

hint4.content: I wonder what should go in here?

hintLevel11.content: Help Boop get all of the satellite parts into the bin.

hintLevel12.content: Get the satellite parts to the bin before they hit the ground.

hintLevel13.content: Use your super wheels to jump over these canyons.

hintLevel14.content: Take photos, collect soil samples, and get the parts to the bin.

hintLevel15.content: Get the bin into space using your tractor beam.

hintLevel16.content: Avoid the asteroids and space junk and get to Mars.

hintLevel17.content: Get Boop safely to the other side of the rock formation, near the soil sample.

hintLevel17B.content: Get the satellite parts to the bin.

hintLevel18.content: Avoid the asteroids and get to the satellite.

hintLevel19.content: Collect all the parts and return them to the satellite.

hintLevel2.content: Help Jet 2 jump over the rocks.

hintLevel20.content: Protect the satellite from incoming asteroids using your new vortex control.

hintLevel3.content: Help Jet 2 get over the construction yard.

hintLevel4.content: Help Jet 2 put all the trash in the bin.

hintLevel5.content: Help Jet 2 put all the trash in the bin.

hintLevel6.content: Get the mysterious item out of the tree.

hintLevel7.content: Get all the satellite parts and trash into the proper bins.

hintLevel8.content: Get Boop to the other side of the Martian hills.

jetBeam.content: Jet 2 does not need to go into space.

journal-full.content: Choose a picture that you don't want to keep, and your new picture will replace it.

journal-none.content: You have not saved the control panel layout.
Next time you finish creating a control panel,
tap the camera in the bottom left corner to take a picture.

journal-some.content: Tap on a picture to see one of your saved control panels.

journal-trash.content: Choose a picture to throw away.

level12Break.content: This would be a good time to get the parts to the bin before more start to fall.

level12More.content: Looks like more parts are about to come down.  Get ready!

level12NoBadge.content: Sorry, too many parts hit the ground for a badge.

level17B.content: Now we need to get all the satellite parts into one place.
Use the tractor beam again to pick up two parts and drop them into the bin.

level17C.content: Finally, we need to lift the satellite part bin into space, like we did on Earth.

levelEnd.content: Nice work!  Tap to go to the next mission.

lsEarth.content: In these levels, you'll control Jet 2 on the Earth.

lostPart.content: You lost your part.  Grab it again and get it back to the satellite.

lsMars.content: In these levels, you'll control Boop on the surface of Mars.

lsSpace.content: In these levels, you'll control your spaceship around Earth,

missPhoto.content: You didn't take a photo of what you were aiming at.

morePhotos.content: There are still more photos to take.

moreSatPart.content: There are still some more satellite parts to put in the bin.

moreSatPart2.content: There are still more parts to bring back to the satellite.

moreSoil.content: You still need to collect more soil samples.

moreTrash.content: There is still more trash to put in the bin.

pointOutProgress.content: This shows how many pieces of trash you need to find.

star.content: You just found a star.  There's a star hidden in every level.
See if you can find them all!

stillMore.content: Nice work!  There are still more to complete for this mission though.

story1.content: My analysis shows that this is part of a satellite near Mars!
I wonder how it got here.
Anyway, let's drop it into the bin so it can be picked up later.

trashCollect.content: Items you suck up with your vacuum will appear here.
Use the throw control to toss some items back out.
You'll find this useful for more than just putting things in bins.

tutorial1.content: Drag controls from here, into the control panel here.
You have limited space for your controls, so rearrange them to fit just right.
The order doesn't matter, just make sure that
you have the controls you need for your mission.

tutorial2.content: When you are ready to control Jet 2,
press the power button to activate the control panel.

tutorial6.content: You've got a new control: Super Jump!
Let's try it out and see if it can help us complete this mission.

tutorial5.content: There's also some new controls that Jet 2 can use.
You don't always need every control,
but sometimes you can use them for extra fun,

tutorial4B.content: Also, if you ever need a reminder about what your mission is,

tutorial4.content: There's a new control panel we can use: Jump!
Drag it into the control panel so Jet 2 can jump over the rocks.

tutorial3.content: You just activated the control panel!
Press the buttons in the panel, and help Jet 2 complete his mission.
If you need to rearrange your controls,
press the power button again to deactivate the control panel.

2000.info: The start game event is triggered at the very beginning of the game (after the game finishes loading). This is used to compute things like time spent in game.

args.info: millisecond count since start of game
args.name: game_time

args.info: session event counter
args.name: event_count

args.info: number of the current round or 0. increments whenever a new level is started
args.name: round

args.info: version identifier for the current build of the game
args.name: version

args.info: list of levels unlocked by previous playthroughs
args.name: unlocked_levels

args.info: list of names and unlock status of each badge in this game[{"name":"some badge", "unlocked":False, "progress":0.33}, ]
args.name: badge_status

2010.info: The end game event occurs when the player exits the game. This is used to compute things like time spent in game.

args.info: millisecond count since start of game
args.name: game_time

args.info: session event counter
args.name: event_count

args.info: number of the current round or 0. increments whenever a new level is started
args.name: round

args.info: name of the robot used in the current round or emptry string if no round
args.name: robot

args.info: identifier of the level layout. 1 - 20
args.name: level_id

args.info: the duration of the game session in milliseconds. Time between start game and end game.
args.name: duration

args.info: home', 'navigation', 'exit' - if the user left the game via clicking the home button, navigating to a new page, or closing the application/browser
args.name: exit_type

args.info: object containing recipe names and unlock status for each level_id in this game{"earth-1":True, "mars-8": False, }
args.name: unlocked_levels

args.info: list of names and unlock status of each badge in this game[{"name":"some badge", "unlocked":False, "progress":0.33}, ]
args.name: badge_status

2020.info: The start round event is triggered at the start of a round when the starts a new platforming section. This event provides information about the game characteristics of the round (i.e. resources, objectives, setup). It is used in calculating things like time spent in a round (for speed and accuracy), attempts at solving a round, and the number of rounds the player has visited (exposures).

args.info: millisecond count since start of game
args.name: game_time

args.info: session event counter
args.name: event_count

args.info: number of the current round or 0. increments whenever a new level is started
args.name: round

args.info: name of the robot used in the current round or emptry string if no round
args.name: robot

args.info: identifier of the level layout. 1 - 20
args.name: level_id

args.info: the layout of robot buttons when the round starts[{"name": "move_right", "position": {x,y}, "shape": [[1,1,1], [0,1,1], [1,1,1]]}, ]
args.name: layout

args.info: list of robot buttons available this round[{"name": "move_right", "shape": [[1,1,1], [0,1,1], [1,1,1]]}, ]
args.name: available_buttons

args.info: list of objectives required to complete this round[{"name": "compost items", "count":3}, ...]
args.name: objectives

args.info: was this round loaded from the screenshot gallery?
args.name: from_gallery

args.info: standardized data layout for brainpoint support
args.name: enlearn_components

2030.info: The beat round event is triggered when the player finishes a round by successfully completing the objectives of the round. This event is used for calculating time spent in a round (for speed and accuracy), attempts at solving a round, and the number of rounds the player has completed (completion).

3010.info: The system-initiated instruction event occurs when the game delivers instructions to the player. It contains information that describes the content of the instruction. This event differs from events 3020 and 3021 as it captures instructions that are not given in response to player action. These events are used to determine the effectiveness of the instructions. We can answer questions like, "did players who received instruction X do better than those who did not?"
